text: Reese Hanneman (born December 25, 1989) is an American cross-country skier. He competed in the 2018 Winter Olympics. He is a 5-time U.S. National Champion, and competed for the United State of America on the FIS World Cup over 8 seasons. ==References== Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Cross-country skiers at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:American male cross-country skiers Category:Olympic cross-country skiers of the United States
